# 4. Objects

Objects store data as key-value pairs.

### Syntax

```javascript
let student = {
    name: "Apeksha",
    age: 20,
    marks: 85
};
```

---

# 5. Access Object Properties

### Dot Notation

```javascript
console.log(student.name);
console.log(student.age);
```

### Bracket Notation

```javascript
console.log(student["marks"]);
```

---

# 6. Update Object Property

```javascript
student.marks = 90;
```

---

# 7. Add New Property

```javascript
student.branch = "IT";
```

---

# 8. Delete Property

```javascript
delete student.age;
```

---

# 9. Object Methods

Methods are functions inside objects.

```javascript
let student = {
    name: "Apeksha",

    greet: function(){
        console.log("Hello");
    }
};

student.greet();
```

